A vintage-style illustration of an antique brass clockwork mechanism filled with intricate gears and cogs, sitting atop weathered blueprints and engineering schematics spread across a mahogany desk. The clockwork device is partially disassembled, revealing layers of complexity within—tiny nested components, delicate springs, and precision-machined parts that suggest decades of accumulated craftsmanship. Warm amber light from an old green-shaded banker's lamp casts dramatic shadows across the scene. A worn leather-bound ledger lies open nearby with hand-drawn diagrams. The color palette features sepia tones, aged brass, deep mahogany browns, and touches of oxidized copper green. The mood evokes careful measurement and valuation of intricate, long-developed machinery—suggesting the weighing of accumulated technical investment and hidden complexity.
